name: A game at chess [manuscript], 1624 August 13.
description: Copy dated one day before last performance on August 14, 1624 before Middleton’s play was banned. Scribal copy in the hand of Ralph Crane lacking portions of the text. Correction in Middleton’s hand (p. 32), as well as corrections in other hands, probably made by later owners. Poems listed in the Folger card index of first lines. Title from title page. Known as the "Archdall" manuscript. Portions also available as a digital reproduction. Also available on microfilm. Mervyn Archdall MS. Formerly Folger MS 7043.

name: A game at chesse : as it hath bine sundrey times acted at the Globe on the Banck side.
description: Anonymous. By Thomas Middleton. In verse. The title page (leaf A1) is engraved and illustrated. Publication date and actual place of publication conjectured by STC and addendum. Signatures: A-I⁴. Also available as a digital reproduction.
disambiguatingDescription: Imperfect: lacking title page (A1). With engraved title page inserted from STC 17882 or 17883 [inserted leaf 2] and the explanation of the illustration (also from STC 17882 or 17883) inlaid to face t.p. [inserted leaf 1]. Manuscript note on front fly-leaves signed "[W Safe. ?]". Calf binding by W. Pratt; all edges gilt. Provenance: armorial bookplate of F. A. Marshall (motto "nunquam sedeo"); anonymous armorial bookplate with manuscript note "1886. [Wase ?]"; coat of arms stamped on A2v of the Duke of Roxburghe
